&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an &lt;strong&gt;Analytical Chemist&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;to join our Global R&amp;amp;D Analytical Services team in Barcelona.&amp;nbsp;This is a&lt;strong&gt; temporary position&lt;/strong&gt; with an expected duration of 6 to 9 months.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This laboratory-based role will support a strategic project focused on expanding the analytical testing performed on incoming raw materials and implementing new analytical methods. The position offers the opportunity to work in a highly regulated environment, supporting multiple R&amp;amp;D and manufacturing initiatives across the business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Perform analytical testing of raw materials against established specifications and compendial methods, particularly USP monographs.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Execute routine and non-routine laboratory analyses using chromatographic and basic analytical techniques.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Develop, implement, optimize, and validate analytical methods.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Investigate quality and manufacturing issues, providing analytical expertise and data-driven recommendations.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Support raw material qualification and alternative sourcing initiatives.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Author technical reports and maintain accurate laboratory documentation.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Ensure proper maintenance, calibration, cleanliness, and organization of laboratory equipment and work areas.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Collaborate closely with cross-functional teams including Product Development, Regulatory Affairs, Safety, Quality, and Manufacturing.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Qualifications&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Degree in Chemistry or a related scientific discipline. Candidates with a higher vocational qualification and extensive relevant laboratory experience will also be considered.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 3–5 years of experience in Analytical R&amp;amp;D or Quality Control laboratories.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;

